# Touch AI - Implementation Walkthrough

I have successfully updated the Touch AI project to include all your requested features! Here is a summary of what was built and how you can use it.

## 1. Floating Desktop Widget (Electron)

The React web app has been transformed into a native Windows desktop widget using **Electron**.
- **Always On Top:** The UI is no longer a website. It is a sleek, glowing, transparent orb that floats in the bottom right corner of your screen.
- **Glassmorphism Panel:** When you click the orb, it smoothly expands into a futuristic dark glass panel where you can control the assistant.
- **Running It:** Open a terminal in the `frontend` folder and run `npm run dev`. This will launch both Vite and the Electron window simultaneously.

## 2. Smooth Gestures & Tab Swiping

The `hand_tracker.py` engine has been heavily upgraded:
- **Steady Mouse:** I implemented an Exponential Moving Average (EMA) filter. This acts like a stabilizer, completely removing the jitter you usually get with MediaPipe, making the mouse control feel incredibly smooth and precise.
- **Swipe for Tabs:** By tracking the velocity of your wrist, you can quickly swipe your hand left or right to switch browser tabs automatically (`Ctrl+Tab` / `Ctrl+Shift+Tab`).

## 3. "Google Lens" Screen Selection Mode

You can now use a gesture to literally draw a box on your screen and have the AI analyze it!
1. **Enter Lens Mode:** Hold up your Thumb and Pinky while keeping your other fingers closed (the "Shaka" 🤙 sign). The camera will detect this and enter Lens Mode.
2. **Draw a Box:** Once in Lens Mode, pinch your thumb and pinky together. A green bounding box will start drawing on the screen. Drag it to cover the text or image you want to search.
3. **Analyze:** When you release the pinch, the app takes a screenshot of that specific area and saves it to `backend/vision/lens_capture.png`.
4. **AI Trigger:** The backend automatically detects the new capture, sends it to the Gemini Vision API, and the Voice Assistant will speak the result/summary out loud!

> [!IMPORTANT]  
> **API Key Required:** To use the Google Lens feature, you must set your Gemini API key as an environment variable (`GEMINI_API_KEY`) before running the backend. If it's not set, the app will still take the screenshot but will give a dummy voice response.

## 4. Voice Commands & Desktop Automation

The `assistant.py` and a new `desktop_env.py` module now work together to automate your computer:
- **"Open Chrome" / "Open Notepad"**: The system will automatically launch the requested apps.
- **"Search YouTube for [query]"**: The assistant will open your browser and search YouTube for whatever you said.
- **"Play Music" / "Pause Music"**: Toggles your system's media playback.
- **"Increase Volume" / "Mute"**: Controls the system volume.
- **"Shutdown system please"**: Initiates a 10-second shutdown sequence.

## Next Steps to Test

1. Open a terminal in the `backend` folder and run `python app.py` (ensure you have set the `GEMINI_API_KEY` in your terminal first if you want to test the Vision feature).
2. Open another terminal in the `frontend` folder and run `npm run dev`.
3. The floating orb will appear on your desktop. Click it to open the panel, and start the Voice and Gesture engines!
